-- GLC Hires Goldman Sachs’s Chetan Bhandari as Managing Director
-- B y   B e t h   J i n k s
-- 2013-02-12T13:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-12/glc-hires-goldman-sachs-s-chetan-bhandari-as-managing-director.html
GLC Advisors & Co., the advisory arm
of Global Leveraged Capital, hired  Chetan Bhandari  as a managing
director from  Goldman Sachs Group Inc. , expanding the firm’s
restructuring advisory practice.  Bhandari was previously a managing director in the
leveraged finance group at Goldman Sachs in Hong Kong and New
York, GLC said an e-mailed statement. At GLC he will focus on
debt advisory, private placement and restructuring services,
based in New York.  GLC Advisors is adding to a restructuring advisory team
that has worked on more than 150 transactions involving $300
billion of securities, according to the firm’s website. Chairman
 Thomas Benninger  founded GLC in 2005 after heading the
restructuring group at  UBS AG , and has recruited bankers from
UBS’s restructuring team including  Soren Reynertson .  Before Goldman Sachs, Bhandari was a managing director with
UBS in the restructuring and leveraged finance groups where he
worked with Benninger and Reynertson. Earlier he worked at DLJ
in the restructuring and leveraged finance teams. Bhandari is a
graduate of Brown University and Harvard Business School.  To contact the reporter on this story:
